CHANGELOG.md:57:- Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:59:- Added depth-2 sensory journal daemon processing (frac-0033): `my-claw/tools/sensory_journal_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers for reading fused organism state, normalizing Theramini/room/mood snapshots, detecting ordered Theramini-start, room-transient, and energy-shift events, writing through the existing `senseweave.sensory_journal` JSONL contract, and running the loop with `max_iterations` / `--once` for tests and smoke runs. `tests/test_sensory_journal_daemon.py` pins import safety, meaningful event descriptions, one-cycle journal writes, and duplicate suppression across repeated active cycles; the existing sensory journal suite and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:61:- Added depth-2 voice alias report helpers (frac-0032): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/voice_aliases.py` now exposes frozen `VoiceAliasEntry` and `VoiceAliasReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `voice_namespace`, `voice_alias_family`, `is_aliased_voice`, `iter_alias_pairs`, `aliases_for_target`, `alias_chain`, `build_voice_alias_entry`, `build_voice_alias_report`, and `summarize_voice_alias_report` so runtime/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing eleven-entry `RUNTIME_VOICE_ALIAS` table into a JSON-safe summary with ordered source/target voices, namespace counts (core vs senseweave), family counts (struck_tonal, metallic, granular, drum, other), senseweave-variant and core-alias counts, unique-target count, target-to-sources mapping, and per-alias entries flagging `is_senseweave_variant` and `is_changed`. Existing `resolve_runtime_voice_name` lookup behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_voice_aliases_depth.py` pins helper outputs, frozen entry/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with `resolve_runtime_voice_name`, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_voice_aliases.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:63:- Added depth-2 synthesis architecture registry report helpers (frac-0031): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis_architecture_registry.py` now exposes frozen `ArchitectureProfile` and `ArchitectureRegistryReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `affinity_band`, `control_span_band`, `fallback_chain`, `build_architecture_profile`, `build_architecture_registry_report`, and `summarize_architecture_registry_report` so planner/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing six-family synthesis strategy registry into a JSON-safe summary with ordered architecture IDs, phase winners, phase-ranked candidates, role-to-architecture mappings, fallback chains, macro-control defaults/span bands, high-affinity phase bands, missing coverage diagnostics, and per-architecture profiles. Existing registry entries and lookup behavior remain unchanged; `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry_depth.py` pins helper cutpoints, fallback-cycle handling, profile/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with existing lookup helpers, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
