# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Added depth-2 breath-to-filter end-to-end test coverage (frac-0061): `tests/test_breath_to_filter.py` now ships a `TestBreathToFilterEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public breath-to-filter API (`estimate_breath_rate`, `breath_phase`, `breath_to_filter_params`, `breath_to_visual_params`) through complete synthetic listening paths. The new tests sweep multiple sine-breath BPMs (3, 6, 12) end-to-end through rate estimation, phase extraction, and filter/visual parameter derivation; assert the documented neutral output for flat and empty RMS histories; sweep a phase table (0.0–1.0) to verify cutoff peaks at inhale (0.25) and troughs at exhale (0.75), resonance peaks at extremes (0.0/0.5), and visual scale/brightness mirror the breath wave; check the documented `min(rate/15, 1.0)` mix-saturation curve across rate steps from 0 to 30 BPM; round-trip filter and visual outputs through `json.dumps`; render JSON-safe diagnostics across calm/fast/flat/noisy signal types; verify rate-detection tolerance per BPM, deterministic pipeline output, and a spot-check of the cosine cutoff curve at known phase extremes. `tests/test_breath_to_filter_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 26 real functions versus 24 trivial). Existing breath-to-filter assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/breath_to_filter.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (4392 tests, 3 skipped, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.

- Added depth-2 audio-analysis end-to-end test coverage (frac-0060): `tests/test_audio_analysis.py` now includes `TestAudioAnalysisEndToEnd`, which drives the existing pure `audio_analysis` public API through complete synthetic listening paths. The new tests analyze tonal sine signals through amplitude, autocorrelation pitch, note/key mapping, content classification, and spectral peak extraction; classify deterministic speech-like dynamic material; retain a sparse impulse through click-transient detection and transient classification; derive silence/onset/sustain/release transitions from windowed RMS values; and confirm public outputs can be serialized into JSON-safe diagnostics. `tests/test_audio_analysis_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 21 trivial functions versus 24 real). Existing audio-analysis assertions and `my-claw/tools/audio_analysis.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.

